[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating metadata requirements**\n\nI'm considering the implications of missing native metadata for the RawEncodedKeySpec public constructor. If it’s absent, does that mean both processes fail? I think Forge should generate the necessary metadata here. But wait, we aren't modifying the metadata. The native tests seem to run with the existing metadata already generated. For new dynamic access call sites, it appears that the Native Image needs to reflect metadata before execution. It's a bit complex!\n\n**Considering test class structure**\n\nI’m thinking about how to approach the structure of test classes. It seems I might want to avoid using nested test classes. I’ll check the existing tests, particularly at the bottom of the BCElGamalPublicKeyTest, to see if there are private static classes being used as helpers. That could give me some insights into what works better in terms of structure.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03afb7d7103368600169fc01e19b9c81a180c2bb19846e8da1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_AHx5c5YhPJ0sUScrqeXmvjh0o7KcpKDk-Wr_67QmRyD4lssCcYyBSHNF9M8LoF1cc4PsjqLihEA1nnPUT3cWA0q_Q7Wo4LQuoQM0UqdbehwLWQZwdxag1N2sgTIA7xEWmGVlissGSs0MPuLO4lNq41BSTRONzKLOZnqSYdyW57xQVHLVD3fTOa4cIR-R4hbTAOKs1Yq0R3S_Hudqo37dmQZ8fZqmveaSVop_Zjn6TmQyDpaFOr9mvuxIgliuOm5GEAKZo86xtSrN0dCZ_9XQp6fLZtw-WqHNnEHuigFFszSM__V81jmbAJCg9_Asiqgklix1GlIwHK43dcmmI01VreRWJZF-fd7Ic9xNGUaXto6Thv8-CBSRRNruUkr8SA_iAcuK1MnSDEDXbSPVDT8ngKV9BgNMre1WMRTTON-yEdIr08Fe5Ji3qa-x-eP5hEZhTy9t6SmOPuYTntz1iewL9G0Lk1Am-y_8QjCrGas-OxFggS3c-74HEosKmZwlX9s5utwiEW0d5vQVcCJXf0Gwzsa7V1cMSWxgklnSCQJkOCEtKqWsLjqjADotnyMRE70tEjkhmL1Q_T6kYO-9g9AMJJ1A6cUmrcSso9AbCzphq-z3M6K8PN8sN45gXrSWOVnBXoEkPt5mo2OsrbU-B5rqk0jpWJ4JDlGjNBlCKQXwFBZZLYfn_7cQjpDviQN3An02Rc0CxaCAH9zbzeprcezPwCxQ0TlnNvXbtKmvVGuRf7idaxuc_ehLcsUhMt-WJtijA5pWRbZUBG1zKK4yRm2Ivj5riQqsMzqThYkYRhl_zlJmBlQf8aEkou4CMx4AKvEA-UtPMw